radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated up to 1.1 cm with a large amount of adjacent fat stranding and small amount of free fluid. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation without focal lesions. The pancreas has normal attenuation without focal lesions. The spleen is surgically absent. The kidneys are normal in size with no focal renal lesions. The stomach and bowel are within normal limits. There is a small amount of free fluid in the pelvis.
